instNote: ﻿Besides the usual branches of a solid English education, the modern languages are taught, vocal and instrumental music, drawing, and painting etc. The terms for board and tuition are $250 per annum. The vacancies for the present year, which commenced on the first Monday in September, and will close early in July, are all filled, most of the pupils being Protestants. They have, moreover, a select day-school in the Institution.

persNote: ﻿The substantial and ornamental branches of education are taught under the direction of Mother Beatrice, Prioress of the Institution. Although this Institution has been but a short time in existence, it has been favored with kind patronage of both Catholics and Protestants, owing chiefly to the energy and perseverance of the Rev. Emanuel Hartig, O.S.B., Pastor of the Mission.

instNote: ﻿Under the patronage of St. Philip Neri, for boys and girls
